task.summary: Default task
fixed more bugs, added logic to stop batch expansion after height threshold, rolled up iterators into single for loop (sad)

renamed functions, made number of top_children dynamic based on parent height (earlier in game = 7, mid game = 5, mid-latter = 3; numbers based on statistics taken when training NN, will titrate based on performance)
added threading for asynchronous policy net eval and cried the whole time.
added threading for tree parallelization so MCTS is always informed by NN (best approach so far). will play with pruning of lower rank children and summing of legal children instead of top children
fixing pernicious threading bugs

moved lock to keep threads from waiting too long, cleaned code, set human v computer player to be able to switch colors and to use different MCTS variants, removed double softmax in NN building, cleaned/added comments
broke up/merged some functions. made the pruning cutoff based on the probability from the NN.
fixed bugs from refactoring
keep searching even if doomed just in case.
removed huge UCTS for win/loss nodes. reduced UCT_multiplier from NN output, playing with exact weight. filter not on top children, but strictly on over 30% or within 10% of best child probability
made best_child_val the best legal child's val (forgot the policy net is model free, so a top choice may be an illegal move)
Comments for the different MCTS variants
more comments, broke up functions, integrated MCTS async into the options and had it use existing expansion wrt NN just in case we cared to use it in the future
made the stochasticity for multithreading a stochastic function of stage in the game, so that later stages are less likely to explore
works great now. too great...
fixed human v computer move. debugging pipe to play wanderer

testing EBFS MCTS (the king is back)
porting back to windows
